      "text": "# [[Platform Economy]]: The Nordic Model?\n\nThe Nordic countries are renowned for their strong labour laws. Yet the entrance of platform firms – especially those we associate with the 'gig economy' – has been at odds with this tradition. In a few isolated instances, some of these platforms have reached collective agreements with unions. Our [https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/rego.12465 open-access article] of the week explores what we should expect, and considers whether some kind of 'Nordic model' of platform regulation is likely to emerge.\n\nArticle by Anna Ilsøe, Carl Fredrik Söderqvist\n\nFeatured in The Machinist"
